You ought to put up a banner, "Frontera,
Texas - Gateway to Inexpensive Pussy. "

823
00:52:56,160 --> 00:52:58,230
That kind of talk doesn't help.

824
00:52:59,160 --> 00:53:02,152
I'd rather have that
than a 10-foot-high catfish statue.

825
00:53:02,240 --> 00:53:04,959
<i>Eddie Richter at the Sentinel
will kill that story.</i>

826
00:53:06,120 --> 00:53:07,473
The Perdido thing?

827
00:53:07,600 --> 00:53:09,716
He agreed it wasn't exactly news.

828
00:53:10,520 --> 00:53:12,750
Danny will be out for blood the next time.

829
00:53:12,840 --> 00:53:16,594
That's why we need to talk to you
about the new jail.

830
00:53:16,760 --> 00:53:18,830
Come on, we don't need a new jail.

831
00:53:19,120 --> 00:53:20,678
That's a matter of opinion.

832
00:53:20,760 --> 00:53:23,513
We're already renting cells to the Feds
for their overflow.

833
00:53:24,040 --> 00:53:28,750
It wouldn't be your construction company
who'd get the bid on building this thing?

834
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:31,274
And, Jorge...

835
00:53:32,400 --> 00:53:35,073
You wouldn't be thinking
about a couple dozen new jobs...

836
00:53:35,160 --> 00:53:38,550
...to dangle by the voters when you run
for mayor next election?

837
00:53:38,800 --> 00:53:41,598
Damn it, Sam! The people
are concerned about crime.

838
00:53:41,880 --> 00:53:44,553
I'm not gonna campaign
against your deal here.

839
00:53:44,920 --> 00:53:46,239
But if anybody asks...

840
00:53:46,320 --> 00:53:49,995
...I've got to tell them the truth.
We don't need a new jail.

841
00:53:50,240 --> 00:53:51,389
We backed you...

842
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:54,278
When you backed me,
you needed somebody named Deeds...

843
00:53:54,360 --> 00:53:56,715
...to bump the other fella out of office.

844
00:53:59,760 --> 00:54:01,955
- Hey, folks.
- Fenton, what's up, buddy?

845
00:54:02,480 --> 00:54:05,040
- How you doing?
- Let's get this thing over with.

846
00:54:16,120 --> 00:54:19,430
I never thought I'd see a buddy of mine
dating a woman...

847
00:54:19,640 --> 00:54:21,596
...with three bars on her shoulder.

848
00:54:21,680 --> 00:54:23,557
It's beyond what you'd call dating.

849
00:54:23,640 --> 00:54:25,358
You're going to get married?

850
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:26,395
Maybe.

851
00:54:26,480 --> 00:54:27,913
You met her family?

852
00:54:29,040 --> 00:54:31,554
They gonna be cool
about you being a white guy?

853
