about those things, it's like a betrayal.

932
00:59:21,680 --> 00:59:23,352
But Fernando did okay.

933
00:59:23,480 --> 00:59:24,754
He dropped out.

934
00:59:24,840 --> 00:59:29,231
Fernando wasn't pissed off at everybody.
He just wanted to fix their cars.

935
00:59:31,480 --> 00:59:34,950
I spent my first 15 years
trying to be just like Buddy.

936
00:59:35,360 --> 00:59:38,079
The next 15 trying
to give him a heart attack.

937
00:59:45,560 --> 00:59:47,949
So, why did you come back here, Sam?

938
00:59:51,360 --> 00:59:52,918
I got divorced...

939
00:59:55,680 --> 00:59:58,558
...and I wouldn't work
for my father-in-law anymore.

940
00:59:59,760 --> 01:00:01,751
And the fellas down here...

941
01:00:02,600 --> 01:00:04,511
...they said they'd back me.

