<i>After that cabrón, Charlie Wade.</i>

1015
01:07:52,360 --> 01:07:54,828
I heard Wade was a bit tough
on the Mexicans.

1016
01:07:59,400 --> 01:08:02,631
He murdered Eladio Cruz.
Is that tough enough for you?

1017
01:08:04,960 --> 01:08:06,154
Murdered him?

1018
01:08:06,320 --> 01:08:09,039
Chucho Montoya saw it with his own eyes.

1019
01:08:10,600 --> 01:08:12,158
Shot him in cold blood.

1020
01:08:12,240 --> 01:08:14,310
<i>Charlie Wade was a big asshole.</i>

1021
01:08:15,720 --> 01:08:16,630
Sam...

1022
01:08:19,440 --> 01:08:20,429
Wait up.

1023
01:08:24,960 --> 01:08:26,154
You're out early.

1024
01:08:27,640 --> 01:08:30,473
Haven't seen much of you at the jail lately.

1025
01:08:30,640 --> 01:08:32,790
Well, I'm working on a few things.

1026
01:08:33,360 --> 01:08:35,749
I'm going over to the other side.

1027
01:08:36,720 --> 01:08:37,948
Republicans?

1028
01:08:38,160 --> 01:08:39,593
No, Mexico.

1029
01:08:40,600 --> 01:08:42,318
Got to talk to someone.

1030
01:08:42,880 --> 01:08:44,552
They got telephones.

1031
01:08:44,720 --> 01:08:45,630
No.

1032
01:08:45,960 --> 01:08:47,632
It's got to be in person.

1033
01:08:54,440 --> 01:08:55,759
The Committee...

1034
01:08:56,320 --> 01:08:58,709
Jorge and Fenton and all, they...

1035
01:08:59,280 --> 01:09:00,599
...they've asked me-

1036
01:09:00,680 --> 01:09:03,035
They want you to stand for sheriff
next election.

1037
01:09:04,600 --> 01:09:05,555
Yeah.

1038
01:09:07,120 --> 01:09:08,553
You'd do a good job.

1039
01:09:10,040 --> 01:09:11,029
Thanks.

1040
01:09:12,280 --> 01:09:13,508
What about you?

1041
01:09:14,120 --> 01:09:16,031
I don't know if I'll still want it.

1042
01:09:19,720 --> 01:09:22,109
I just didn't want to go around your back.

1043
01:09:22,240 --> 01:09:23,958
I appreciate you telling me.

1044
01:09:27,240 --> 01:09:28,753
You think we need a new jail?

1045
01:09:32,200 --> 01:09:33,519
Well, Sam...

1046
01:09:34,600 --> 01:09:36,670
It's a complicated issue.

1047
01:09:38,800 --> 01:09:39,915
Yeah, Ray.

1048
01:09:41,240 --> 01:09:43,231
You'd be a hell of a sheriff.

1049
01:10:34,720 --> 01:10:35,755
Down here...

1050
01:10:35,840 --> 01:10:38,718
...we don't throw everything away
like you gringos do.

1051
01:10:40,760 --> 01:10:42,273
Recycling, right?

1052
01:10:43,960 --> 01:10:45,473
We invented that.

1053
01:10:46,240 --> 01:10:48,993
The government doesn't have
to tell people to do it.

1054
01:10:51,400 --> 01:10:53,277
You own this place, huh?

1055
01:10:55,080 --> 01:10:56,399
This place...

1056
01:10:56,680 --> 01:10:58,591
...the one across the street...

1057
01:10:59,480 --> 01:11:01,948
...three or four others in Ciudad León.

1058
01:11:06,400 --> 01:11:07,958
"King of the Tires. "

1059
01:11:09,960 --> 01:11:13,714
A lot of your people rolling over that bridge
on my rubber.

1060
01:11:14,160 --> 01:11:16,276
You lived in the States for a while?

1061
01:11:17,160 --> 01:11:18,115
Fifteen years.

1062
01:11:18,880 --> 01:11:20,632
Made some money, came back here?

1063
01:11:22,440 --> 01:11:23,714
Something like that.

1064
01:11:24,720 --> 01:11:28,156
Hey, you ever know
a fella named Eladio Cruz?

1065
01:11:31,080 --> 01:11:33,469
You're the sheriff of Rio County, right?

1066
01:11:47,520 --> 01:11:49,078
Step across this line.

1067
01:11:56,200 --> 01:11:58,714
You're not the sheriff of nothing anymore.

1068
01:11:59,680 --> 01:12:03,798
<i>Just some tejano with a lot of questions
I don't have to answer.</i>

1069
01:12:04,800 --> 01:12:06,313
A bird flying south...

1070
01:12:07,160 --> 01:12:09,071
...you think he sees this line?

1071
01:12:09,760 --> 01:12:11,830
<i>Rattlesnake,jabalina...</i>

1072
01:12:12,800 --> 01:12:14,233
...whatever you got.

1073
01:12:15,160 --> 01:12:18,675
You think halfway across that line
they start thinking different?

1074
01:12:19,240 --> 01:12:20,798
Why should a man?

1075
01:12:21,800 --> 01:12:24,712
Your government's been pretty happy
to have that line.

1076
01:12:25,600 --> 01:12:27,989
The question's just been where to draw it.

1077
01:12:33,080 --> 01:12:35,913
My government can go fuck itself
and so can yours.

1078
01:12:37,840 --> 01:12:39,910
I'm talking about people here.

1079
01:12:40,080 --> 01:12:41,069
Men.

1080
01:12:47,320 --> 01:12:48,639
Eladio Cruz...

1081
01:12:49,480 --> 01:12:52,995
<i>...is giving his friends a lift one day
in his camión.</i>

1082
01:12:53,240 --> 01:12:56,676
<i>But since they're on one side
of this invisible line and not the other...</i>

1083
01:12:56,760 --> 01:12:59,479
<i>...they got to hide
in the back como criminales.</i>

1084
01:12:59,720 --> 01:13:03,395
<i>And because over there
he's just another Mex bracero...</i>

1085
01:13:03,600 --> 01:13:05,716
<i>...any man with a badge is his jefe.</i>

1086
01:14:13,960 --> 01:14:15,234
What's in the back?

1087
01:14:15,320 --> 01:14:17,834
<i>Not much,jefe. Some watermelons.</i>

1088
01:14:18,360 --> 01:14:20,316
I'm driving them up to the market.

1089
01:14:20,400 --> 01:14:22,277
They could bring a good price.

1090
01:14:25,600 --> 01:14:28,478
I heard somebody's been hauling wets
on this road.

1091
01:14:29,880 --> 01:14:32,030
I haven't seen anybody doing that.

1092
01:14:33,560 --> 01:14:35,915
That person's been bragging
all over the county...

1093
01:14:36,000 --> 01:14:39,276
...how he doesn't have to cut
that gringo sheriff in on it.

1094
01:14:39,400 --> 01:14:41,675
Run his own operation without any help.

1095
01:14:43,160 --> 01:14:44,434
<i>What's your name?</i>

1096
01:14:45,080 --> 01:14:46,308
Eladio Cruz.

1097
01:14:48,240 --> 01:14:51,073
You know this road's got a bad reputation.

1098
01:14:51,680 --> 01:14:52,874
Reputation?

1099
01:14:53,040 --> 01:14:54,632
<i>Bandidos, Injuns.</i>

1100
01:14:55,920 --> 01:14:59,515
Many an unfortunate soul
has been ambushed out on this stretch.

1101
01:14:59,600 --> 01:15:01,830
I hope you're carrying some protection.

1102
01:15:02,040 --> 01:15:03,268
Protection?

1103
01:15:04,440 --> 01:15:06,476
You carrying a firearm, son?

1104
01:15:06,920 --> 01:15:08,273
Don't lie to me now.

1105
01:15:11,320 --> 01:15:12,389
Just a shotgun.

1106
01:15:13,360 --> 01:15:14,554
Just a shotgun.

1107
01:15:15,240 --> 01:15:17,196
Then let me have a look at that.

1108
01:15:30,160 --> 01:15:33,436
Little greaser son of a bitch is running
a goddamn bus service.

1109
01:15:33,520 --> 01:15:36,034
Thinks he can make a fool
out of Charlie Wade.

1110
01:15:36,400 --> 01:15:38,356
Get them wets out of the back.

1111
01:15:38,440 --> 01:15:39,839
See what we've got.

1112
01:15:44,200 --> 01:15:45,633
You killed him!

1113
01:15:46,320 --> 01:15:48,914
You got a talent
for stating the obvious, son.

1114
01:16:18,600 --> 01:16:19,749
Steve called for you.

1115
01:16:19,840 --> 01:16:20,795
Steve?

1116
01:16:21,080 --> 01:16:24,755
Steve. Board of Education Steve,
who likes you.

1117
01:16:25,480 --> 01:16:28,950
He goes for us hot-blooded Mexican girls,
I can tell.

1118
01:16:29,200 --> 01:16:31,760
Spanish. My mother would have
a heart attack.

1119
01:16:32,040 --> 01:16:33,917
Your mother's family is Spanish?

1120
01:16:34,000 --> 01:16:35,718
They go back to Cortés.

1121
01:16:35,800 --> 01:16:39,952
When he was riding by they were squatting
in a hut cooking hamsters for dinner.

1122
01:16:40,240 --> 01:16:43,710
You've got to be interested in somebody.
All you do is work.

1123
01:16:44,040 --> 01:16:46,952
All my mother does is work.
It's how you get to be Spanish.

1124
01:16:47,040 --> 01:16:48,678
How about this sheriff?

1125
01:16:49,080 --> 01:16:50,115
Sheriff?

1126
01:16:50,240 --> 01:16:52,435
The old high-school heartthrob sheriff?

1127
01:16:52,520 --> 01:16:54,636
I thought you were crazy about each other.

1128
01:16:54,720 --> 01:16:56,950
He's available. You're available.

1129
01:16:57,840 --> 01:17:00,229
I'm unmarried. I'm not available.

1130
01:17:00,400 --> 01:17:02,960
You told me one time it was true love.

1131
01:17:06,160 --> 01:17:08,594
Nobody stays in love for 23 years.

1132
01:17:44,600 --> 01:17:45,555
Let's go.

1133
01:17:47,440 --> 01:17:48,509
Goddamn it.

1134
01:17:49,920 --> 01:17:51,148
Come here. Come on.

1135
01:17:51,240 --> 01:17:54,471
- What the hell are you doing, asshole?
- How old is that girl?

1136
01:17:55,480 --> 01:17:57,516
Get your clothes in order, missy.

1137
01:17:57,600 --> 01:17:59,079
Where's your goddamn sense?

1138
01:17:59,160 --> 01:18:01,674
You got no fucking right!
Stay out of my life!

1139
01:18:02,680 --> 01:18:04,193
Give me the goddamn car keys.

1140
01:18:04,280 --> 01:18:05,633
What should I do with her?

1141
01:18:05,720 --> 01:18:08,439
Drive her home. Tell her mother
where we found her.

1142
01:18:08,640 --> 01:18:10,949
- Leave her alone!
- Move it, boy!

1143
01:18:14,320 --> 01:18:16,550
Don't tell my mother. She'll kill me.

1144
01:18:16,640 --> 01:18:17,595
Pilar!

1145
01:18:17,920 --> 01:18:19,273
Don't eye me.

1146
01:18:19,360 --> 01:18:20,395
Git!

1147
01:21:09,040 --> 01:21:10,189
Follow me.

1148
01:21:35,560 --> 01:21:38,279
We thought we were something, didn't we?

1149
01:21:41,320 --> 01:21:42,309
Yeah.

1150
01:21:45,360 --> 01:21:47,874
And I look at my kids in school...

1151
01:21:48,760 --> 01:21:50,830
...10th, 11th-graders.

1152
01:21:52,360 --> 01:21:54,510
That's who we were. Children.

1153
01:21:59,120 --> 01:22:01,395
I mean, what did we know about anything?

1154
01:22:05,960 --> 01:22:06,995
Nothing.

1155
01:22:10,640 --> 01:22:12,358
When Nando died...

1156
01:22:14,480 --> 01:22:16,072
...it was so sudden...

1157
01:22:18,240 --> 01:22:20,708
...I kind of went into shock for a while...

1158
01:22:22,240 --> 01:22:24,549
...and then I woke up and...

1159
01:22:25,360 --> 01:22:29,831
...there was the rest of my life
and I had no idea what to do with it.

1160
01:22:37,520 --> 01:22:39,909
You know, the other day you asked...

1161
01:22:41,320 --> 01:22:42,958
...why I came back.

1162
01:22:43,680 --> 01:22:44,635
Yeah?

1163
01:22:47,600 --> 01:22:49,670
I came back 'cause you were here.

1164
01:23:10,880 --> 01:23:13,997
My mother hasn't changed a song
since I was 10.

1165
01:25:44,640 --> 01:25:46,710
How come it feels the same?

1166
01:25:49,000 --> 01:25:50,399
I don't know.

1167
01:25:51,360 --> 01:25:52,952
It just feels good.

1168
01:25:55,480 --> 01:25:56,754
Always did.

1169
01:26:04,440 --> 01:26:05,395
So...

1170
01:26:09,080 --> 01:26:11,514
What are we going to do about this?

1171
01:26:16,040 --> 01:26:17,029
More...

1172
01:26:18,160 --> 01:26:19,309
...I hope.

1173
01:26:47,680 --> 01:26:49,716
How long have you lived here?

1174
01:26:57,720 --> 01:26:58,869
Two years.

1175
01:26:59,800 --> 01:27:02,030
There's nothing on the walls.

1176
01:27:02,640 --> 01:27:03,959
No pictures.

1177
01:27:05,600 --> 01:27:06,953
I don't have kids.

1178
01:27:11,160 --> 01:27:12,673
Other pictures...

1179
01:27:14,360 --> 01:27:17,193
I don't know. It's nothing I want
to look back on.

1180
01:27:18,360 --> 01:27:20,157
Like your story's over.

1181
01:27:22,520 --> 01:27:24,272
I've felt that way...

1182
01:27:25,080 --> 01:27:25,876
...yeah.

1183
01:27:27,520 --> 01:27:28,589
It isn't.

1184
01:27:31,480 --> 01:27:32,595
Not by a long shot.

1185
01:27:37,080 --> 01:27:38,308
Pilar...

1186
01:27:42,800 --> 01:27:44,711
What was your father's name?

1187
01:27:45,680 --> 01:27:46,669
Eladio.

1188
01:27:47,640 --> 01:27:48,914
Eladio Cruz.

1189
01:28:37,400 --> 01:28:38,833
That's John Horse.

1190
01:28:39,920 --> 01:28:42,229
The Spanish down in Florida call him...

1191
01:28:42,400 --> 01:28:43,753
..."Juan Caballo. "

1192
01:28:45,200 --> 01:28:46,394
John Horse.

1193
01:28:47,320 --> 01:28:48,958
He a black man or an Indian?

1194
01:28:49,040 --> 01:28:50,029
Both.

1195
01:28:50,960 --> 01:28:52,791
He was part of the Seminole nation.

1196
01:28:52,880 --> 01:28:56,395
Got pushed down into the Florida
Everglades back in pioneer days.

1197
01:28:57,160 --> 01:28:59,993
African people run off from slaveholders...

1198
01:29:00,360 --> 01:29:01,873
...hooked up with them...

1199
01:29:01,960 --> 01:29:04,030
...married up, had children.

1200
01:29:05,240 --> 01:29:07,879
When the Spanish gave up Florida...

1201
01:29:07,960 --> 01:29:11,396
...the U.S. Army come down
to move all the Indian people to Oklahoma.

1202
01:29:11,600 --> 01:29:13,033
A couple of them held out.

1203
01:29:13,400 --> 01:29:15,470
That man, John Horse...

1204
01:29:15,560 --> 01:29:17,949
...his friend, Wildcat, another fella named...

1205
01:29:18,040 --> 01:29:19,314
...Osceola...

1206
01:29:19,520 --> 01:29:21,112
...formed a fighting band...

1207
01:29:21,200 --> 01:29:24,033
...held out for another 10, 15 years...

1208
01:29:24,480 --> 01:29:28,234
...and beat Zach Taylor and 1,000 troops
at Lake Okeechobee.

1209
01:29:30,080 --> 01:29:31,638
So they stayed in Florida?

1210
01:29:31,720 --> 01:29:34,632
One night they packed up,
rode out to Mexico.

1211
01:29:35,720 --> 01:29:38,792
Men went to work
for General Santa Anna down there.

1212
01:29:40,320 --> 01:29:44,518
After the Civil War they came north
to Texas, put up at Fort Duncan...

1213
01:29:44,840 --> 01:29:49,072
...and the men joined what was called
the Seminole Negro Indian Scouts.

1214
01:29:49,320 --> 01:29:50,435
The best trackers...

1215
01:29:50,520 --> 01:29:54,149
...on either side of the border.
They chased after bandits...

1216
01:29:54,760 --> 01:29:58,230
...rustlers, Texas rednecks,
Kiowas, Comanches...

1217
01:29:58,800 --> 01:30:00,916
They fought against the Indians?

1218
01:30:01,000 --> 01:30:02,513
Just like they did in Mexico.

1219
01:30:02,600 --> 01:30:04,318
But they were Indians themselves.

1220
01:30:05,200 --> 01:30:06,872
They were in the Army...

1221
01:30:07,120 --> 01:30:08,553
...like your father.

1222
01:30:11,520 --> 01:30:13,112
You know who I am?

1223
01:30:15,040 --> 01:30:16,871
I got a pretty good guess.

1224
01:30:17,800 --> 01:30:19,028
That guy who got shot.

1225
01:30:20,160 --> 01:30:22,754
You didn't go telling your father
you were here?

1226
01:30:22,920 --> 01:30:24,194
Are you kidding?

1227
01:30:24,680 --> 01:30:26,432
And face a court-martial?

1228
01:30:28,920 --> 01:30:30,114
Pretty tough old man.

1229
01:30:30,680 --> 01:30:32,432
Every time he moves up a rank...

1230
01:30:32,520 --> 01:30:35,398
...he tightens the screws a little more.
Just 'cause...

1231
01:30:36,560 --> 01:30:38,312
You know, he didn't have...

1232
01:30:40,360 --> 01:30:41,918
Didn't have a father.

1233
01:30:43,520 --> 01:30:45,431
He's still pissed off about it.

1234
01:30:47,560 --> 01:30:49,232
When you're his age...

1235
01:30:50,600 --> 01:30:53,160
...you'll still be pissed off about him.

1236
01:30:57,200 --> 01:30:58,918
How come you got into this?

1237
01:31:01,760 --> 01:31:03,432
These are our people.

1238
01:31:04,040 --> 01:31:07,749
There are Paynes in Florida,
Oklahoma, Piedras Negras-

1239
01:31:08,560 --> 01:31:09,788
So I'm part Indian?

1240
01:31:10,280 --> 01:31:11,872
By blood you are.

1241
01:31:13,280 --> 01:31:15,111
But blood only means what you let it.

1242
01:31:15,760 --> 01:31:19,594
My father says from the day you're born
you start from scratch.

1243
01:31:20,520 --> 01:31:21,350
No breaks.

1244
01:31:21,440 --> 01:31:22,509
No excuses.

1245
01:31:24,520 --> 01:31:26,670
You got to pull yourself up on your own.

1246
01:31:27,600 --> 01:31:29,830
He's living proof of that, son.

1247
01:31:31,920 --> 01:31:33,353
Living proof.

1248
01:31:41,200 --> 01:31:42,633
'Morning, Hollis.

1249
01:31:42,800 --> 01:31:43,789
Sam!

1250
01:31:43,880 --> 01:31:45,108
Sit down.

1251
01:31:46,360 --> 01:31:48,271
Big to-do the other day.

1252
01:31:49,560 --> 01:31:51,835
Meant a lot to folks you said something.

1253
01:31:52,640 --> 01:31:54,596
You thought anymore about our murder?

1254
01:31:56,400 --> 01:32:00,109
I wish I could tell you I remembered
something new, but I can't.

1255
01:32:03,360 --> 01:32:05,590
Well, I got an idea what happened.

1256
01:32:05,960 --> 01:32:06,949
You do?

1257
01:32:09,440 --> 01:32:13,399
I think somewhere between
Roderick Bledsoe's club and his house...

1258
01:32:13,480 --> 01:32:15,550
...Wade ran into Buddy Deeds.

1259
01:32:16,480 --> 01:32:18,550
I think Buddy put a bullet in him.

1260
01:32:18,880 --> 01:32:22,236
Waited for him to die,
threw him in the trunk of the sheriff's car...

1261
01:32:22,320 --> 01:32:24,675
...and drove him out by Fort McKenzie.

1262
01:32:26,120 --> 01:32:29,954
I think he buried him under four feet
of sand and never looked back.

1263
01:32:34,440 --> 01:32:36,635
You lived in the man's house, how long?

1264
01:32:37,600 --> 01:32:39,352
17, 18 years...

1265
01:32:40,640 --> 01:32:43,598
...but didn't get to know him
any better than that.

1266
01:32:44,560 --> 01:32:47,393
I got to go see somebody
up in San Antonio.

1267
01:32:49,560 --> 01:32:51,790
Now, your memory gets any better...

1268
01:32:52,000 --> 01:32:53,911
...I'll be back tonight.

1269
01:33:07,400 --> 01:33:09,038
She finally got up.

1270
01:33:10,360 --> 01:33:11,713
It's Saturday.

1271
01:33:12,200 --> 01:33:13,918
You got in late last night.

1272
01:33:14,320 --> 01:33:15,673
I had some...

1273
01:33:16,560 --> 01:33:18,357
...some school business.

1274
01:33:20,840 --> 01:33:22,034
Could I get this?

1275
01:33:23,720 --> 01:33:24,755
Paloma.

1276
01:33:25,120 --> 01:33:27,156
Nobody really wears that stuff.

1277
01:33:27,520 --> 01:33:30,557
Just 'cause you went to Catholic school
and wore a uniform.

1278
01:33:30,640 --> 01:33:32,870
I only went for my last two years.

1279
01:33:33,320 --> 01:33:34,594
How come?

1280
01:33:36,720 --> 01:33:39,234
My mother wanted
to keep me away from...

1281
01:33:41,880 --> 01:33:43,074
...from boys.

1282
01:33:43,960 --> 01:33:45,234
Did it work?

1283
01:33:48,920 --> 01:33:51,992
Longhorns go for 10 times the price.

1284
01:33:53,400 --> 01:33:56,039
But longhorns are hard
to come by these days.

1285
01:33:57,040 --> 01:33:58,439
Sell much out here?

1286
01:33:59,000 --> 01:34:01,833
How am I going to sell things?
Nobody comes around.

1287
01:34:02,160 --> 01:34:03,832
This stretch of road...

1288
01:34:03,920 --> 01:34:06,115
...runs between Nowhere and...

1289
01:34:06,760 --> 01:34:08,239
...Not Much Else.

1290
01:34:09,000 --> 01:34:11,070
A hell of a spot to put a business.

1291
01:34:11,760 --> 01:34:13,876
Don't see much competition, do you?

1292
01:34:15,040 --> 01:34:17,395
Used to sell these things like hotcakes.

1293
01:34:17,480 --> 01:34:18,595
Now...

1294
01:34:19,000 --> 01:34:22,197
...if it can't play those disks,
they won't look at it.

1295
01:34:23,480 --> 01:34:24,913
I like it here.

1296
01:34:25,840 --> 01:34:28,479
Once I tried going
onto the reservation to live.

1297
01:34:28,560 --> 01:34:30,278
Couldn't take the politics.

1298
01:34:30,360 --> 01:34:33,079
Damn Indians will drive you crazy
with that.

1299
01:34:36,000 --> 01:34:39,231
Now, your father,
this wasn't what he had in mind.

1300
01:34:40,520 --> 01:34:42,112
He come out of Korea...

1301
01:34:42,240 --> 01:34:44,959
...bought a Chevy with too much engine.

1302
01:34:45,400 --> 01:34:49,996
Used to come roaring up and down
this road all hours of the day and night...

1303
01:34:50,240 --> 01:34:52,231
...looking for somebody to race.

1304
01:34:57,520 --> 01:34:58,475
Here.

1305
01:34:59,760 --> 01:35:01,318
Buffalo chips.

1306
01:35:01,840 --> 01:35:03,558
A fella down in Santa Fe told me...

1307
01:35:03,640 --> 01:35:07,235
...he sells these as fast
as a buffalo can squeeze them out.

1308
01:35:12,960 --> 01:35:15,520
You think he killed anybody in Korea?

1309
01:35:16,720 --> 01:35:20,395
They don't hand those medals out
for hiding in your foxhole.

1310
01:35:23,160 --> 01:35:24,559
Would you buy this?

1311
01:35:26,800 --> 01:35:27,710
No.

1312
01:35:28,960 --> 01:35:30,791
Yeah, neither would I.

1313
01:35:32,560 --> 01:35:35,154
If he hadn't found the deputy's job...

1314
01:35:36,240 --> 01:35:40,597
...I believe Buddy might've gone down
the other path, got into serious trouble.

1315
01:35:41,080 --> 01:35:42,798
It settled him right down.

1316
01:35:42,880 --> 01:35:44,552
That and your mother.

1317
01:35:48,560 --> 01:35:50,835
Of course, he had that other one later.

1318
01:36:00,080 --> 01:36:01,593
He had another woman?

1319
01:36:03,400 --> 01:36:07,154
Your mother was not one
to be chased off her patch.

1320
01:36:07,800 --> 01:36:10,189
Half the damn county knew about it.

1321
01:36:11,000 --> 01:36:14,231
Nobody thought the worse of her
for seeing it through.

1322
01:36:14,320 --> 01:36:15,878
You know who it was?

1323
01:36:16,600 --> 01:36:17,874
The other one?

1324
01:36:18,600 --> 01:36:19,430
At my age...

1325
01:36:19,920 --> 01:36:21,273
...you learn a new name...

1326
01:36:21,360 --> 01:36:23,271
...you got to forget an old one.

1327
01:36:23,760 --> 01:36:24,715
Here.

1328
01:36:26,880 --> 01:36:30,429
This big fella was sleeping
in a crate at Cisco's junkyard.

1329
01:36:30,920 --> 01:36:33,957
When I was going to open
to see what was in her...

1330
01:36:34,240 --> 01:36:36,310
...jumped right at my face.

1331
01:36:37,320 --> 01:36:40,596
Scared me so bad I had to kill him
without thinking.

1332
01:36:41,080 --> 01:36:44,709
Be careful where you go poking.
Who knows what you'll find.

1333
01:37:22,120 --> 01:37:23,633
Private Johnson...

1334
01:37:26,240 --> 01:37:28,356
...are you unhappy...

1335
01:37:29,200 --> 01:37:30,269
...in the Army?

1336
01:37:30,480 --> 01:37:31,549
No, sir.

1337
01:37:33,000 --> 01:37:35,036
Then how would you explain...

1338
01:37:35,240 --> 01:37:37,356
...that out of 120 people...

1339
01:37:37,480 --> 01:37:39,311
...you were the only one...

1340
01:37:39,400 --> 01:37:41,595
...who tested positive for drugs?

1341
01:37:41,680 --> 01:37:43,159
I'm sorry, sir.

1342
01:37:45,400 --> 01:37:48,119
When you were given
the opportunity to enlist...

1343
01:37:48,560 --> 01:37:51,677
...a kind of contract was agreed upon.

1344
01:37:51,760 --> 01:37:54,479
I think the Army has honored its part...

1345
01:37:54,600 --> 01:37:55,794
...of that agreement.

1346
01:37:55,880 --> 01:37:56,835
Yes, sir.

1347
01:37:56,960 --> 01:37:59,520
Do you believe in
what we do in here, Private?

1348
01:38:00,120 --> 01:38:01,917
I can do the job, sir.

1349
01:38:08,680 --> 01:38:12,036
What exactly do you think your job is?

1350
01:38:14,160 --> 01:38:16,469
Follow orders, do whatever they say.

1351
01:38:16,680 --> 01:38:17,829
Who's "they"?

1352
01:38:18,920 --> 01:38:20,399
The officers.

1353
01:38:20,480 --> 01:38:21,959
And that's the job?

1354
01:38:22,760 --> 01:38:25,035
Nothing about serving your country?

1355
01:38:27,880 --> 01:38:30,519
These are not trick questions,
Private Johnson.

1356
01:38:30,920 --> 01:38:32,319
You'll get an Article 15...

1357
01:38:32,400 --> 01:38:35,472
...and we'll go through the process
one way or another.

1358
01:38:36,080 --> 01:38:38,389
I'm just trying to understand...

1359
01:38:39,720 --> 01:38:41,950
...how someone like you thinks.

1360
01:38:43,080 --> 01:38:44,798
You really want to know?

1361
01:38:44,960 --> 01:38:45,915
Please.

1362
01:38:48,320 --> 01:38:52,154
It's their country. This is one
of the best deals they offer.

1363
01:38:54,560 --> 01:38:56,790
How do you think I got to be a colonel?

1364
01:38:57,160 --> 01:38:59,628
Being good at your job.
Doing what they tell you.

1365
01:38:59,720 --> 01:39:01,073
Do what they tell you?

1366
01:39:01,160 --> 01:39:03,116
I mean, follow orders, sir.

1367
01:39:07,400 --> 01:39:09,630
With your attitude, Private...

1368
01:39:10,440 --> 01:39:12,795
...I'm surprised you want to stay
in the service.

1369
01:39:13,320 --> 01:39:14,469
I do, sir.

1370
01:39:15,200 --> 01:39:16,474
Because it's a job?

1371
01:39:18,720 --> 01:39:21,109
Outside it's such a mess. It's...

1372
01:39:25,680 --> 01:39:26,590
Chaos.

1373
01:39:29,800 --> 01:39:31,199
Why do you think...

1374
01:39:33,160 --> 01:39:35,390
...they let us in on the deal?

1375
01:39:38,880 --> 01:39:43,351
'Cause they got people to fight:
Arabs, yellow people, whatever.

1376
01:39:43,440 --> 01:39:45,158
Might as well use us.

1377
01:39:52,480 --> 01:39:54,391
It works like this, Private.

1378
01:39:55,200 --> 01:39:58,510
Every soldier in the war
doesn't have to believe...

1379
01:39:58,960 --> 01:40:00,791
...in what he's fighting for.

1380
01:40:01,560 --> 01:40:05,838
Most of them fight just to back up
the other soldiers in their squad.

1381
01:40:07,040 --> 01:40:08,951
You try not to get them killed.

1382
01:40:09,040 --> 01:40:11,349
You try not to get them extra duty.

1383
01:40:11,680 --> 01:40:14,035
You try not embarrass yourself...

1384
01:40:14,800 --> 01:40:16,233
...in front of them.

1385
01:40:29,720 --> 01:40:31,631
Why don't you start with that?

1386
01:40:32,600 --> 01:40:33,635
Yes, sir.

1387
01:40:37,800 --> 01:40:38,915
Dismissed.

1388
01:40:40,680 --> 01:40:42,079
Thank you, sir.

1389
01:41:16,880 --> 01:41:21,112
<i>This time, Fred Zenito for Pager
and the Aggies jump to a 14-point lead.</i>

1390
01:41:21,240 --> 01:41:23,470
<i>Sooners back to punt on their own 27.</i>

1391
01:41:24,800 --> 01:41:29,237
Longhorns are going to kick some serious
butt this Saturday. You just watch.

1392
01:41:29,560 --> 01:41:33,473
We got a kid, a tailback from
down your way, out of El Indio-

1393
01:41:34,000 --> 01:41:35,479
That's in Maverick County.

1394
01:41:36,040 --> 01:41:37,473
Right, and you're in?

1395
01:41:37,560 --> 01:41:38,549
In Rio.

1396
01:41:38,800 --> 01:41:40,552
This kid, Hosea Brown...

1397
01:41:40,640 --> 01:41:42,073
...he does the 40 in 3.4.

1398
01:41:42,160 --> 01:41:44,799
Soft hands, lateral movement,
the whole package.

1399
01:41:44,880 --> 01:41:47,348
- Only a sophomore.
- Still go to all the home games?

1400
01:41:47,440 --> 01:41:51,274
Daddy's got his box in the stadium
and I'll fly to the Cowboy away games.

1401
01:41:51,720 --> 01:41:54,075
And Friday nights there's high school.

1402
01:41:54,160 --> 01:41:57,675
Churchill's got this boy, 6 foot 6,
310, moves like a cat.

1403
01:41:57,840 --> 01:42:01,230
High school, we're talking.
Guess how much he can bench-press?

1404
01:42:01,680 --> 01:42:02,954
Bunny, you...

1405
01:42:03,560 --> 01:42:05,278
You on that same medication?

1406
01:42:05,520 --> 01:42:07,272
- Why, do I seem jumpy?
- No.

1407
01:42:07,600 --> 01:42:09,750
You look good. I was just wondering.

1408
01:42:10,200 --> 01:42:13,749
Last year was awful with Mama passing on
and this business with O.J.

1409
01:42:13,840 --> 01:42:15,671
It's not Don Meredith or...

1410
01:42:15,760 --> 01:42:18,718
...one of our boys,
but it kind of threw me for a loop.

1411
01:42:18,960 --> 01:42:20,188
You look good.

1412
01:42:20,720 --> 01:42:23,234
Then that squeaker,
the Aggies dropped to Oklahoma.

1413
01:42:23,320 --> 01:42:27,279
That son of a bitch stepped in some
lucky shit before he kicked that goal.

1414
01:42:27,640 --> 01:42:31,269
If they hadn't pulled me off that woman,
I'd have jerked a knot in her.

1415
01:42:32,880 --> 01:42:34,359
Were you in a fight?

1416
01:42:35,320 --> 01:42:37,515
Daddy calls it an altercation.

1417
01:42:38,280 --> 01:42:40,475
How you doing, Sam? You look skinny.

1418
01:42:41,080 --> 01:42:43,594
No, I'm the same weight I always was.

1419
01:42:44,920 --> 01:42:47,912
Daddy hired a pinhead to take your job.
Says so himself:

1420
01:42:48,120 --> 01:42:51,192
"Even my son-in-law was better
than this pinhead I got now. "

1421
01:42:51,280 --> 01:42:52,349
Bunny...

1422
01:42:54,600 --> 01:42:57,068
That stuff I left in the garage still there?

1423
01:42:58,520 --> 01:43:02,069
Least he never called me that.
With me it was always "high-strung. "

1424
01:43:02,160 --> 01:43:05,630
"Bunny would've done something
with her life if she wasn't so high-strung. "

1425
01:43:05,720 --> 01:43:07,278
Or "tightly wound. "

1426
01:43:07,880 --> 01:43:10,314
You haven't had one of your fires,
have you?

1427
01:43:11,440 --> 01:43:15,149
The stuff I left in the garage,
some of it was my father's.

1428
01:43:15,920 --> 01:43:17,797
Did you watch the draft this year?

1429
01:43:19,320 --> 01:43:22,471
Of course not. Idiot question.
They try to make it dramatic...

1430
01:43:22,560 --> 01:43:25,358
...like it's a surprise who picks who
in the first round...

1431
01:43:25,440 --> 01:43:29,592
...but they went over it for months
with their experts, computers...

1432
01:43:29,800 --> 01:43:32,678
...doctor's reports, coach's evaluations...

1433
01:43:32,840 --> 01:43:36,116
...highlight reels, psychological profiles...

1434
01:43:36,840 --> 01:43:41,470
I wouldn't be surprised if they collected
stool samples on them, had them analyzed.

1435
01:43:41,640 --> 01:43:42,993
All that to pick...

1436
01:43:43,080 --> 01:43:45,196
...a football player for your squad.

1437
01:43:46,080 --> 01:43:50,198
Compared to that, what you know about
a person when you get married to them...

1438
01:43:50,280 --> 01:43:52,635
...doesn't amount to diddly, does it?

1439
01:43:55,360 --> 01:43:56,998
No, I suppose not.

1440
01:43:57,480 --> 01:44:00,950
You kind of bought yourself
a pig in a poke, didn't you?

1441
01:44:01,960 --> 01:44:06,670
The whole time we were seeing each other,
you didn't know that I was tightly wound.

1442
01:44:07,040 --> 01:44:08,951
It wasn't just you, Bunny.

1443
01:44:09,960 --> 01:44:11,712
No, it wasn't, was it?

1444
01:44:13,040 --> 01:44:16,476
You didn't exactly throw yourself
into it heart and soul.

1445
01:44:19,400 --> 01:44:22,836
Your shit's still in the garage,
if that's what you came for.

1446
01:44:34,600 --> 01:44:36,511
Three hundred and fifty pounds.

1447
01:44:40,320 --> 01:44:44,029
That boy Churchill's got.
He plays tackle both ways.

1448
01:44:46,440 --> 01:44:48,590
Bench-presses 350 pounds.

1449
01:44:51,360 --> 01:44:54,158
Imagine having that much weight on you,
pressing down.

1450
01:44:54,240 --> 01:44:56,800
Be hard to breathe, hard to swallow.

1451
01:44:58,120 --> 01:45:01,874
I think they have another fella there
to keep it off your chest.

1452
01:45:03,840 --> 01:45:04,955
A spotter.

1453
01:45:06,000 --> 01:45:09,356
"I only got my little girl now," he says.

1454
01:45:09,560 --> 01:45:11,198
"She's my lifeline. "

1455
01:45:13,000 --> 01:45:16,788
Then he says I can't sit in the box anymore
if I don't control myself.

1456
01:45:17,280 --> 01:45:18,269
Son of a bitch!

1457
01:45:18,360 --> 01:45:21,318
He doesn't even watch the games,
just sits there drinking.

1458
01:45:21,400 --> 01:45:22,992
Looks up at the TV now and then.

1459
01:45:23,080 --> 01:45:26,629
I'd be better off in the cheap seats
with some real football people.

1460
01:45:27,480 --> 01:45:29,072
You look good, Bunny.

1461
01:45:30,440 --> 01:45:32,158
It was nice to see you.

1462
01:45:34,720 --> 01:45:35,675
Thanks.

1463
01:45:37,480 --> 01:45:39,869
I like it when you say that, Sam.

1464
01:46:04,200 --> 01:46:05,713
"Dearest Buddy. "

1465
01:46:16,280 --> 01:46:17,918
Hey, it's the general.

1466
01:46:19,560 --> 01:46:21,755
Colonel. Is Otis in?

1467
01:46:21,920 --> 01:46:23,512
- Come on in.
- If it's too late-

1468
01:46:23,600 --> 01:46:24,794
Come on in.

1469
01:46:33,080 --> 01:46:37,232
Otis is sitting up with some people
at the club. I don't think he'll be long.

1470
01:46:45,040 --> 01:46:47,998
His hot sauce recipe
won a contest last year.

1471
01:46:48,400 --> 01:46:50,072
They're selling it as far away...

1472
01:46:50,160 --> 01:46:51,479
...as San Antonio.

1473
01:46:52,440 --> 01:46:54,874
You've been in this house for a while?

1474
01:46:55,600 --> 01:46:59,798
I've been here with him eight years.
He built it when he was with Leora.

1475
01:47:00,720 --> 01:47:02,039
Never met her.

1476
01:47:02,840 --> 01:47:05,070
There's a bunch of them you never met.

1477
01:47:05,240 --> 01:47:06,832
Well, me neither.

1478
01:47:08,600 --> 01:47:10,830
Let me show you around.

1479
01:47:25,360 --> 01:47:28,591
He got into this cowboys-and-Indians stuff
a while back.

1480
01:47:28,880 --> 01:47:30,359
Spent half his time poking...

1481
01:47:30,440 --> 01:47:32,749
...around the library, way up to Austin.

1482
01:47:52,720 --> 01:47:54,676
Kind of like a shrine, isn't it?

1483
01:47:56,760 --> 01:47:58,716
Where did he get all this stuff?

1484
01:47:58,880 --> 01:48:00,757
Your mother's got a brother, Alphonse.

1485
01:48:01,600 --> 01:48:02,430
Uncle Al.

1486
01:48:02,520 --> 01:48:06,195
Otis stood on good terms with him.
Whenever you make the news...

1487
01:48:06,320 --> 01:48:07,639
...he sends it on.

1488
01:48:08,280 --> 01:48:10,157
When they made you general...

1489
01:48:10,360 --> 01:48:13,033
...Otis almost drove away
our customers going on about it.

1490
01:48:13,120 --> 01:48:14,394
I'm a colonel.

1491
01:48:14,960 --> 01:48:15,915
I know.

1492
01:48:16,560 --> 01:48:19,313
The man made me memorize
the whole Army chain of command...

1493
01:48:19,400 --> 01:48:21,038
...before he'd marry me.

1494
01:48:25,000 --> 01:48:27,639
My mother said that
he never asked about me.

1495
01:48:29,000 --> 01:48:30,592
He never asked her.

1496
01:48:40,800 --> 01:48:42,313
Tell him I stopped by?

1497
01:48:42,920 --> 01:48:43,955
Thanks.

1498
01:48:48,280 --> 01:48:49,508
Catch you later...

1499
01:48:51,280 --> 01:48:52,395
...Colonel.

1500
01:49:23,840 --> 01:49:25,432
<i>Seòora Cruz.</i>

1501
01:49:27,800 --> 01:49:28,869
Who is it?

1502
01:49:32,440 --> 01:49:35,318
What are you doing out here?
Are you crazy?

1503
01:49:39,520 --> 01:49:42,080
In English. We're in the United States.

1504
01:49:42,320 --> 01:49:45,915
I have some friends
and they have had an accident.

1505
01:49:47,160 --> 01:49:49,549
- You have somebody else out there?
- We was...

1506
01:49:49,640 --> 01:49:53,235
...by the river and I heard my friend
calling for help...

1507
01:49:53,760 --> 01:49:55,079
...and I look...

1508
01:49:55,600 --> 01:49:57,431
...and she has fallen in the water.

1509
01:49:57,520 --> 01:49:59,431
Don't tell me lies. What happened?

1510
01:50:01,040 --> 01:50:03,110
We was crossing the river.

1511
01:50:08,480 --> 01:50:10,311
What are you doing out there?

1512
01:50:10,440 --> 01:50:12,715
Wait. Who are they?
Why bring them here?

1513
01:50:12,960 --> 01:50:14,439
<i>I need help, seòora.</i>

1514
01:50:19,840 --> 01:50:22,752
I'll call Border Patrol.
They'll get her to the hospital.

1515
01:50:24,280 --> 01:50:26,589
You think you're doing
these people a favor?

1516
01:50:26,680 --> 01:50:29,319
What are they going to do?
They get on welfare...

1517
01:50:29,400 --> 01:50:31,152
...or they become criminals.

1518
01:50:56,240 --> 01:50:58,117
This girl is a friend of yours?

1519
01:51:00,040 --> 01:51:01,473
I thought you were married.

1520
01:51:01,680 --> 01:51:05,719
I am married to the cousin of a friend
but only to live here.

1521
01:51:06,160 --> 01:51:07,878
This is the mother of my child.

1522
01:51:09,640 --> 01:51:10,629
Typical.

1523
01:51:20,640 --> 01:51:21,675
Homework?

1524
01:51:23,400 --> 01:51:24,879
I finished that.

1525
01:51:25,160 --> 01:51:26,752
I'm just messing around.

1526
01:51:30,760 --> 01:51:31,829
Tanks, huh?

1527
01:51:32,480 --> 01:51:33,754
Yeah, well...

1528
01:51:34,200 --> 01:51:37,715
If you've got to be in the Army,
better to have something slick to drive.

1529
01:51:37,800 --> 01:51:38,755
So...

1530
01:51:39,960 --> 01:51:41,632
You're going in the Army?

1531
01:51:44,280 --> 01:51:46,316
That's the general plan, isn't it?

1532
01:51:51,520 --> 01:51:52,953
That's up to you.

1533
01:51:56,880 --> 01:51:58,950
The Army isn't for everybody.

1534
01:52:05,920 --> 01:52:08,639
It's not that I think
you wouldn't be good at it.

1535
01:52:09,120 --> 01:52:10,235
You know...

1536
01:52:12,440 --> 01:52:16,672
I wouldn't be disappointed if you decided
to do something else with your life.

1537
01:52:19,320 --> 01:52:20,309
You wouldn't?

1538
01:52:22,680 --> 01:52:23,590
No.

1539
01:52:34,360 --> 01:52:36,271
How's your room shaping up?

1540
01:52:37,840 --> 01:52:39,910
It's fine. I'm pretty much moved in.

1541
01:52:40,000 --> 01:52:41,115
Good.

1542
01:52:46,240 --> 01:52:48,117
Are we ever going to see your father?

1543
01:52:48,640 --> 01:52:49,755
My father?

1544
01:52:50,080 --> 01:52:51,274
He lives here, right?

1545
01:52:51,360 --> 01:52:52,475
Yes, he does.

1546
01:52:59,040 --> 01:53:00,473
Maybe we'll...

1547
01:53:01,120 --> 01:53:03,918
We'll fix that thing out back and have...

1548
01:53:04,320 --> 01:53:05,309
...a barbecue.

1549
01:53:06,000 --> 01:53:07,592
We could invite him and...

1550
01:53:07,680 --> 01:53:09,272
...and his wife over.

1551
01:53:12,360 --> 01:53:14,112
He makes his own sauce.

1552
01:54:10,320 --> 01:54:11,753
<i>Let's go! Hurry up!</i>

1553
01:54:13,040 --> 01:54:15,031
Everybody in the world will see.

1554
01:54:18,080 --> 01:54:19,832
He was a doctor on the other side.

1555
01:54:21,680 --> 01:54:22,829
Don't worry about it.

1556
01:54:24,440 --> 01:54:26,192
He owes me a few favors.

1557
01:54:31,800 --> 01:54:34,473
In English, Enrique. In English!

1558
01:54:40,760 --> 01:54:41,749
Hollis!

1559
01:54:45,760 --> 01:54:46,715
Hollis!

1560
01:54:48,960 --> 01:54:50,359
You in there?

1561
01:55:14,160 --> 01:55:15,115
Fellas.

1562
01:55:22,800 --> 01:55:24,233
You're open late.

1563
01:55:24,960 --> 01:55:27,599
I'm not open. We're just talking.

1564
01:55:34,960 --> 01:55:36,871
So, Hollis probably told you.

1565
01:55:37,480 --> 01:55:39,277
We found Charlie Wade.

1566
01:55:40,200 --> 01:55:41,633
Is that right?

1567
01:55:42,720 --> 01:55:46,030
Start digging holes in this county,
no telling what'll come up.

1568
01:55:47,920 --> 01:55:49,751
You two saw it, didn't you?

1569
01:55:52,560 --> 01:55:54,949
You two saw it when Buddy killed him.

1570
01:55:58,800 --> 01:56:01,189
I'm going to find out one way or the other.

1571
01:56:01,800 --> 01:56:04,712
Your father had the finest sense
of justice...

1572
01:56:04,880 --> 01:56:06,757
...of any man I've ever known.

1573
01:56:07,240 --> 01:56:09,151
And my mother was a saint.

1574
01:56:11,280 --> 01:56:13,919
For 15 years the whole damn town...

1575
01:56:14,240 --> 01:56:16,800
...knew he had another woman on the side.

1576
01:56:20,240 --> 01:56:22,834
He stole $10,000
and set her up in business...

1577
01:56:22,960 --> 01:56:24,632
...but hell, what's that?

1578
01:56:25,360 --> 01:56:27,590
You got a problem, old Buddy'll fix it.

1579
01:56:28,080 --> 01:56:30,196
You facing some time in jail?

1580
01:56:30,400 --> 01:56:34,313
Buddy'll knock half of it off,
if you do what he says when he says.

1581
01:56:35,520 --> 01:56:38,034
You got some business
that's not exactly legal?

1582
01:56:38,120 --> 01:56:39,269
Just talk to Buddy.

1583
01:56:39,360 --> 01:56:40,349
Buddy Deeds-

1584
01:56:40,440 --> 01:56:42,192
Buddy Deeds was a murderer.

1585
01:56:44,080 --> 01:56:45,479
That night at the cafe...

1586
01:56:45,840 --> 01:56:48,877
...he didn't stay long after you left,
did he, Hollis?

1587
01:56:50,080 --> 01:56:52,992
Maybe he'd decided
he'd gone too far with Wade.

1588
01:56:53,080 --> 01:56:56,356
He figured he'd better not wait
for the sheriff to get behind him.

1589
01:56:56,440 --> 01:56:58,954
So he stepped out to see
if he could catch up...

1590
01:57:02,280 --> 01:57:04,669
...and you were here that night...

1591
01:57:05,240 --> 01:57:06,878
...weren't you, "O"?

1592
01:57:08,720 --> 01:57:09,948
I was here.

1593
01:57:13,320 --> 01:57:16,517
I'd been running a game
on the side after hours.

1594
01:57:18,280 --> 01:57:19,474
Craps.

1595
01:57:20,160 --> 01:57:22,310
Draw poker on the weekends.

1596
01:57:23,800 --> 01:57:25,870
Roderick didn't know about it.

1597
01:57:26,720 --> 01:57:28,153
More important...

1598
01:57:28,720 --> 01:57:31,280
...Charlie Wade didn't know about it...

1599
01:57:31,640 --> 01:57:34,518
...'cause I didn't want to cut him in on it.

1600
01:57:36,200 --> 01:57:39,237
I was pretty full of myself
back in those days.

1601
01:57:40,400 --> 01:57:44,029
Hell, I just didn't expect the man so early.

1602
01:59:49,920 --> 01:59:50,830
Wade!

1603
02:00:34,920 --> 02:00:38,469
Sheriff Charlie was the whip hand
for old Judge Tibbs...

1604
02:00:38,840 --> 02:00:41,593
...who pretty much owned
this county back then.

1605
02:00:42,600 --> 02:00:44,431
If the truth came out...

1606
02:00:45,040 --> 02:00:47,600
...he wasn't going to go easy on Hollis.

1607
02:00:50,040 --> 02:00:52,679
I don't know why I trusted Buddy with it...

1608
02:00:54,040 --> 02:00:56,076
...don't know why he trusted me.

1609
02:00:59,320 --> 02:01:01,072
The first time I talked with him...

1610
02:01:01,160 --> 02:01:03,116
...was right there and then...

1611
02:01:04,080 --> 02:01:07,914
...with a dead white man leaking blood
on the floor between us.

1612
02:01:08,440 --> 02:01:12,228
The three of us cleaned up
and took him out by the post...

1613
02:01:12,920 --> 02:01:14,399
...and put him under.

1614
02:01:15,600 --> 02:01:17,511
I can't say I was much help.

1615
02:01:18,040 --> 02:01:19,792
And the $10,000?

1616
02:01:20,680 --> 02:01:22,193
Widow's benefits.

1617
02:01:22,880 --> 02:01:25,599
He figured it'd make
the disappearance look better.

1618
02:01:25,720 --> 02:01:29,349
And Mercedes was scraping by
after Charlie killed her man.

1619
02:01:30,800 --> 02:01:31,994
Buddy and her...

1620
02:01:32,080 --> 02:01:34,196
...didn't get hooked up until later.

1621
02:01:35,040 --> 02:01:36,792
Time went on...

1622
02:01:36,880 --> 02:01:38,871
...people liked the story we told...

1623
02:01:38,960 --> 02:01:41,474
...better than what the truth
might have been.

1624
02:01:42,640 --> 02:01:44,232
It's your call, Sam.

1625
02:01:46,160 --> 02:01:49,038
I don't think the Rangers are likely to...

1626
02:01:49,480 --> 02:01:52,199
...find out any more
than they already know.

1627
02:01:55,160 --> 02:01:56,752
And as for me...

1628
02:02:00,080 --> 02:02:02,799
...it's just one of your unsolved mysteries.

1629
02:02:11,680 --> 02:02:14,035
Word gets out who the body was...

1630
02:02:15,080 --> 02:02:17,116
...people'll think Buddy done it.

1631
02:02:20,280 --> 02:02:22,191
Buddy's a goddamn legend.

1632
02:02:23,960 --> 02:02:25,518
He can handle it.

1633
02:02:31,440 --> 02:02:32,873
'Night, fellas.

1634
02:02:59,680 --> 02:03:01,591
When does the picture start?

1635
02:03:04,640 --> 02:03:07,996
Are you going to tell your mother
we've been seeing each other?

1636
02:03:08,400 --> 02:03:10,516
She'll find out sooner or later.

1637
02:03:10,680 --> 02:03:14,150
I don't have to ask permission anymore,
if that's what you mean.

1638
02:03:19,960 --> 02:03:22,394
You have any idea when your father died?

1639
02:03:22,480 --> 02:03:23,435
Eladio?

1640
02:03:24,720 --> 02:03:26,915
Couple of months before I was born.

1641
02:03:29,400 --> 02:03:31,391
Try a year and half.

1642
02:03:50,320 --> 02:03:54,199
Buddy bought the cafe for her
with money he took from the county.

1643
02:03:57,800 --> 02:03:59,756
They can't pull this on me.

1644
02:04:00,840 --> 02:04:02,193
It's not fair.

1645
02:04:07,320 --> 02:04:08,833
I don't believe this.

1646
02:04:15,920 --> 02:04:18,718
He paid the hospital bill
when you were born.

1647
02:04:21,960 --> 02:04:23,188
Your mother...

1648
02:04:24,120 --> 02:04:25,951
...she always called you...

1649
02:04:26,400 --> 02:04:28,152
..."a beautiful daughter"...

1650
02:04:29,240 --> 02:04:31,356
...in the letters she wrote to him.

1651
02:04:38,280 --> 02:04:40,919
From the first time I saw you at school...

1652
02:04:50,320 --> 02:04:53,869
...all those years we were married
to other people, I always felt...

1653
02:04:54,920 --> 02:04:56,751
...like we were connected.

1654
02:05:01,480 --> 02:05:03,152
I remember thinking...

1655
02:05:04,760 --> 02:05:07,035
...you were the one part of my life...

1656
02:05:07,880 --> 02:05:09,996
...that Buddy didn't have a piece of.

1657
02:05:11,120 --> 02:05:13,315
I can't have any more children.

1658
02:05:13,960 --> 02:05:16,110
After Amado, I had complications.

1659
02:05:16,200 --> 02:05:19,636
I can't get pregnant anymore,
if that's what the rule is about.

1660
02:05:23,560 --> 02:05:24,834
So that's it?

1661
02:05:27,080 --> 02:05:29,469
You won't want to be with me anymore?

1662
02:05:32,960 --> 02:05:34,359
If I met you...

1663
02:05:36,040 --> 02:05:38,076
...for the first time today...

1664
02:05:39,320 --> 02:05:41,311
...I'd still want to be with you.

1665
02:05:46,720 --> 02:05:48,472
Start from scratch?

1666
02:05:49,880 --> 02:05:50,790
Yeah.

1667
02:05:52,440 --> 02:05:55,193
All that other stuff and all that history...

1668
02:05:56,080 --> 02:05:57,798
...the hell with it, right?

1669
02:06:03,560 --> 02:06:05,073
Forget the Alamo.

